Imaging of chronic pancreatitis. This article reviews the recognized findings of chronic pancreatitis on CT and endoscopic retrograde cholangiopancreatography. It also discusses more recently developed techniques including gadolinium-enhanced MR imaging, MR cholangiopancreatography, and endoscopic ultrasound. Variants of chronic pancreatitis and difficulties in differentiating pancreatic neoplasms from inflammatory pancreatic masses are also discussed.